<item>HUMAN SHIELD</item>
<item>PAWN</item>
    </list>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">人質</item>
        <item xml:lang="och">質／質子</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>FOREIGNER GIVEN to someone FOR SUPPORTING a PROMISE OR CONTRACT with that person.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The technical term for a hostage is zhì 質, and there are no current competing near synonyms.</p>
        </div>
<div type="huang-jingui">
<p>HUANG JINGUI 2006</p>
<p>TRADE 16.</p>
<p>質，以人或物抵押借貸。</p>
<p>贅，以人作抵押貸錢，起於秦漢。</p>
<p>貼，中古以來以人或物作抵押無息借貸。</p>
<p>當，中古以來指以小巧之物抵押借貸。</p>
<p>典，中古以來指用小巧之物或固定資產甚至人作抵押借貸。</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>人質</p>
<p>質子</p>
<p>質</p>
<p>肉票 (lit, obs) refers in a very traditional way to a hostage.</p>
<p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／</p>
        </div>
